            <p>Philadelphia 18 Feby <hi rend="underline">1886</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Morais&#33;<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
                
            <p>I have seen an article in to day&#39;s<lb/> Ledger commencing A Polish Jew<lb/> arrested on suspicion of having<lb/> choked his wife to death<lb/>  I have observed already very<lb/> often&#44; these papers find some<lb/> pleasure in announcing if it<lb/> is a Jew&#44; they never write a<lb/> Polish Catholic or a Russian<lb/> Protestant or a German Lutheran<lb/> I <sic>dont</sic> feel myself capable to<lb/> write a proper protest to the<lb/> editors of any paper therefore<lb/> I take the liberty to put it in the<lb/> hand of a genuine champion for<lb/> the Jewish &#91;&#63;&#93; and take hereby<lb/> the observation that I <sic>dont</sic><lb/> believe this mentioned names<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>belong to Israelites<lb/></p>
            <p>A protest and investigation about<lb/> this is recommended to you<lb/> By a Israelite<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
